description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced, enthusiastic and proactive Pharmacist to work within our clinical team where patient experience and safety is at the heart of everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will allow you to utilise and develop your skills in both medical and surgical aspects of digestive pharmaceutical care. You will also be working within the Parental Nutrition (PN) Team, and to play an active part in the Trust&#39;s Fluid and Nutrition Committee. With the newly refurbished endoscopic unit, Bedford Hospital is a hub for bowel screening and gastrointestinal surgery, whilst Luton Hospital is active in bariatric surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What about the department I will join?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have recently completed a Pharmacy Transformation Programme to include refurbishment of the department and adoption of the latest technology to include a Chemotherapy EPMA system, automated robotic and controlled drug dispensing and e-Rostering. Clinically you will be supported by mobile technology and electronic systems for pharmacy handover, patient prioritisation and triaging, medicine reconciliation and discharge processing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also participate in late night, weekend and bank holiday rotas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to personal development and you will also have the opportunity to undertake further training relevant to the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
